VI. Roleplaying Profile
Personality: A Firecracker
Ylva is a living whirlwind of joyous energy and infectious enthusiasm. She is loud, laughs from her belly, and shows affection with back-slapping camaraderie that can make a grown Nord stumble. She embodies the heart of a loyal wolf-pupΓÇöboundless energy, fierce devotion to her "pack," and an almost childlike excitement for the simple, profound things she loves: a good fight, a challenging hunt, and a hearty meal (preferably one she butchered herself). Her enthusiasm is as overwhelming as it is genuine, and often slightly terrifying to those not accustomed to it.
Core Motivation: The Thrill of the Hunt
Ylva is a devout follower of Hircine because she believes the Great Hunt is the most exciting game in the world. Her lycanthropy isn't a gift or a curse; it's her favorite toy. She seeks "worthy prey" not out of duty, but for the sheer, unadulterated joy of testing her strength against the world's most dangerous creatures.
The Butcher's Philosophy
She approaches combat and butchery as an enthusiastic artist utterly fascinated by her craft.
"Have you ever seen the way a Sabre Cat's muscles are layered? It's beautiful! Perfect design! Taking it apart is like solving the world's most interesting puzzle. And then you get to eat it! It's the best! The fight is the game, the butchering is the art, and the meal is the prize. What's not to love?"

VII. RECRUITMENT: THE ROAD TO KORVANJUND
Ylva intercepted the party on the road to Korvanjund. She had been tracking the Kynesgrove cultists for three weeks, planning to mount their heads on her wall. When she arrived, the dragon was dead and the cultists were ash. The party had done her work for her.
She planted her axe in the snow, challenged Kyboh to a non-lethal brawl to prove her worth, and talked her way into the group by sheer force of personality. She didn't ask for pay or permission. She invited herself because the mission sounded like an excellent time.
The Secret: Ylva was already a werewolf when she joined the party. She chose not to tell them. She is Hircine's - body, soul, and blood - and has been for years. She hides it behind her boisterous personality, behind the laughter and the axe and the constant motion. The party would have sensed something wrong if they'd paid attention, but Ylva is very good at making people look at her personality instead of her nature.
The Reveal: At Mzinchaleft, when a spider's manipulator leg punched through her shoulder and dropped her to 0 HP, the party saw her transform for the first time. She didn't die - the werewolf mechanic kicked in. Hit 0 HP in human form with an unused transformation = automatic shift. She had to hit 0 again in wolf form to actually die. She didn't. She got back up as a nine-foot werewolf and tore through the spider swarm. The party watched in stunned silence as their cheerful Nord companion became a monster.
The Aftermath: Her armor and clothing were completely shredded by the transformation. She emerged from Mzinchaleft wearing only Saijah's cloak, which she didn't bother to close properly. She was confused, exhilarated, and naked. She didn't seem to care about the naked part. She cared very much about the "I died and came back as a wolf" part. Hircine had claimed her more completely than she realized.

VIII. Combat & Social Profile
Combat Approach
In combat, Ylva is an enthusiastic shock trooper and crowd-control specialist. She joyfully initiates battle, often with a bellowing laugh and a Devastating Charge aimed at the largest foe on the field. When surrounded, she unleashes her Sweep ability or her Master's Form, "Hircine's Merry Dance," with a whoop of delight, seeing the challenge not as a threat, but as the height of the game. She is a one-woman solution to being overwhelmed by superior numbers.
The Beast Within
Her werewolf transformation is not a last resort; it is a celebration. She views it as her "let's get serious and have some real fun" mode, a trump card to be played with glee during the most challenging encounters, such as a boss fight or when the party needs to turn the tide of a desperate battle.
Social Approach
In social situations, Ylva is an unstoppable force of personality. She is the ultimate icebreaker, capable of turning a tense tavern silent with a booming laugh or a friendly challenge to an arm-wrestling match. Her use of Persuasion is less about careful debate and more about overwhelming a target with pure, unadulterated positivity until they agree. Her Intimidation, in contrast, is not a cold threat, but the terrifying friendliness of a predator who doesn't realize how scary her "playful" side truly is.

